#  Bug Report: Uber Login Page - Incorrect Error Message

## Bug ID
BR-001-UBER-LOGIN

## Reported By
Nathan Phelan

## Report Date
2025-06-01

---

## Summary
The Uber login page returns an incorrect error message when an invalid email format is entered. Instead of prompting the user to “Enter a valid email,” the message incorrectly states “Email or password is incorrect.”

---

## Environment
- OS: Windows 11
- Browser: Google Chrome v124.0
- URL: https://auth.uber.com/login
- Device: Desktop

---

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Go to https://auth.uber.com/login  
2. Enter `invalidemail.com` in the email field  
3. Enter any password (e.g., `Test123!`)  
4. Click the **Next** or **Login** button  

---

## Expected Result
> “Please enter a valid email address.”

## Actual Result
> “Email or password is incorrect.”

---

## Severity
🟡 Medium – User may get confused and retry correct credentials without realizing the format is invalid.

---

## Screenshot (Optional)
*Attach screenshot here if available*

---

## Notes
Tested on Firefox as well — same result. Recommend validation for email format before submitting form.

